author: Charles Curtis | For NJ Advance Media
title: WFAN's Mike Francesa loses it trying to explain Mets' playoff rotation to 'dense' fan (AUDIO)
text:
PLUS: Francesa screams 'WIN THE GAME!' at caller 
A caller on Friday tried to argue about how the Mets should use rookie hurler Noah Syndergaard (he thinks it's crazy if the Mets start him twice on the road). Francesa noted Matt Harvey can only pitch once in the opening series against the Los Angeles Dodgers and it devolves into a screaming match. 
Go ahead and click on the video above titled, "Mike Francesa strokes out in glorious fashion." You won't regret it.
